parameters: Even though it's basic, you must not neglect it.

Advanced magic and special-grade magic are created
based on basic magic.

You are already second-year students in the high
school section, but until you graduate, you are
apprentices. Listen carefully.
Today, let's start with a review.

Fontaine-san, please read from page 5 of the
textbook.

Even though it's called basic magic, it seems like
the content becomes more difficult as the classes
progress.

I see, I'm worried if I can keep up because I
don't have basic knowledge.
What kind of magic is Masamune good at?

I specialize in offensive magic. As for the five
major elements, I can at least use fire,
lightning, and water magic.

(I guess my level isn't that high after all. Well,
I am a student who has never been in actual
combat)

As expected of someone who just transferred in. It
seems there isn't much I can teach you.

That's not true. I don't know anything about the
academy.

Hehe, you're humble. If there's anything you don't
understand, feel free to ask me.

(Is this person kind even to guys! They're
actually a pretty nice person)
But compared to Amelia, I'm nothing.

Leon... Did you properly listen to the part where
Elena was reading?

(This is not the time for me to be listening to
class seriously, I need to research about
summoning demons.)
Are there any talented magicians in this class?

Well... if I had to say, it would be Elena and
Hiyo.

Elena may not look like it, but she has excellent
grades. Although she doesn't use magic in front of
others very often.

Hiyo has the top grades in the class. And she's
also a member of the student council.

You can't join our student council if you're not
good at magic.

(Those two, huh? But they don't seem like
geniuses. If that's the case, could they be the
culprits behind the summoning ritual?)

But compared to Vice President Olivia senpai and
Jackson senpai, it's nothing.

Senpai... Are there any amazing wizards in the
third year?

Ah, especially Vice President Olivia is a genius.
She will surely become a magician who leaves her
name in the history of magic.

(I need to investigate Vice President Olivia and
Jackson next time.)
Amelia... Your voice is beautiful too.

Sensei... I know it's not my place to say, but is
it really necessary?
Even though I'm in a position to teach?

Yeah. Magicians who are called geniuses like that
don't become school teachers.

It's either going to the battlefield or creating
my own workshop to research magic.

I heard that Principal Mazers was an amazing
magician, but since he's already an old man, it
seems like he doesn't use magic much anymore.
But what's the point of asking about that?

No, I'm just gathering information. I've only just
transferred here.
